SIMPLE: glorious
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Glorious
<hw>Glo"ri*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>glorios</ets>, <ets>glorious</ets>, F. <ets>glorieux</ets>, fr. L.
<ets>gloriosus</ets>. See <er>Glory</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Exhibiting attributes, qualities, or acts that are
worthy of or receive glory; noble; praiseworthy; excellent; splendid;
illustrious; inspiring admiration; <as>as, <ex>glorious</ex>
deeds</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>These are thy <qex>glorious</qex> works, Parent of good !</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Eager for glory or distinction; haughty; boastful;
ostentatious; vainglorious.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Most miserable⟦br⟧
Is the desire that's <qex>glorious</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Ecstatic; hilarious; elated with drink.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>kings may be blest, but Tam was <qex>glorious</qex>,⟦br⟧
O'er all the ills of life victorious.</q> <rj><qau>Burns.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>During his office treason was no crime,⟦br⟧
The sons of Belial had a <qex>glorious</qex> time.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Eniment; noble; excellent; renowned; illustrious;
celebrated; magnificent; grand; splendid.</syn></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Glo"ri*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Glo"ri*ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>
<rj><au>Udall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Sing ye to the Lord, for he hath triumphed
<qex>gloriously</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Ex. xv. 21.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I speak it not <qex>gloriously</qex>, nor out of affectation.</q>
<rj><qau>B. Jonson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glory</ent>⟦br⟧
